# footballBackEnd -- Project Context

This document captures the full state of the footballBackEnd project as of March 1, 2026. Read this before making any changes.

## What This Project Is

An AWS backend providing REST APIs for NFL player statistics data. It is the backend half of a two-repo application:

- **footballFrontEnd** (`/home/rharwood/workplace/footballFrontEnd`) -- Next.js App Router frontend with a BFF (Backend for Frontend) layer. Still in early foundation phase. Its architecture and auth patterns are documented in `.cursor/rules/` (see `bff.mdc`, `architecture.mdc`, `tech-stack.mdc`).
- **footballBackEnd** (`/home/rharwood/workplace/footballBackEnd`) -- This repo. AWS infrastructure + Lambda APIs + PostgreSQL. **Fully deployed and functional.**

The application scope is **NFL player statistics for the 2023-2025 seasons**. No fantasy team/league features -- just real NFL player data, team rosters, and per-game stats sourced from the ESPN API.

